Hey friends!!!! I’ve missed y’all so much! I’m so excited to exchange conversations in my DM’s with you! It’s definitely what I’ve missed most! Also, the sheer creativity I get to express here is like nothing else I can see, touch or feel!! But……LISTEN!!! My month off this joint was more than I could have EVER imagined it would be!!! The first week was hard but after that, baby, I was drinking water and minding my own business and it was SO SO SO good!!! So I’ve decided to do things a little different here from here on out. You’ll get some of the same stuff from me but I’m gonna take a shift and really be true to who I am. I am a sharer by nature and I just want to continue doing that in more and more authentic ways. I want to show up here how God is calling me and that’s not me sharing links to all the things, plus I’m no good at it 🤣🤣 Will I still share stuff I love, no doubt!!!!!!!! But I’m just gonna do me. Not so much of the crafts and holiday baskets, just more of spilling my heart to you! I hope this content is super relatable and inspires you but also if it’s not, that’s cool too! I promised myself I would no longer do anything just because it is “expected” of me. The fact is, I’ve not seen much coin from this app recently, so nothing is stopping me from doing or saying what I want 🗣️ Ya feel me?!! So let’s chat in the comments!!!! What’s on your mind?! How have y’all been?! Give me all the life updates I’ve missed in the last month. Cause a month off here, feels like 2 years 🤣

Every year we go up a number balloon, I’m absolutely floored!! But this year, the last year before double digits is hits different! Tj said last night that she is half way out of our house and I wanted to shed a tear! How is this going so fast?!! 

Happy 9th Birthday Noelle Taylor 🎉❤️

Birthday party pictures from this weekend coming soon 🥰

On Saturday we celebrated this smart, kind, incredibly talented and artsy child of ours with the Pokémon party of her dreams!! It was so much fun and exactly what she wanted. Thanks to our family and friends for making it out to celebrate our girl! Now, if I hear I’m a “pre-tween” one more time 🤦🏾‍♀️

This time of year is when Tj and I celebrate our anniversary of dating!! This year makes 15 years ❤️💘❤️‍🔥 He was exactly what I needed at a time I wasn’t expecting it. It hit me dead in my mouth with no time to react. This fine man I had been crushing on was chasing after me full speed ahead, with honesty and purity I hadn’t seen before. He was a VISION OF LOVE 💖 #hazleynails #15yearstogether

Nail idea from Pinterest

Listen….don’t knock it until you try it!!! 1 month away felt like 3, Instagram is a time warp!! I was noticing things about my kids that I hadn’t really paid attention to before. Is that a little embarrassing to admit?! Sure, but it’s real! I was so present it felt like parenting in the 90’s must have felt like 🤣 The last thing I want to do is look back on this time of being considered an influencer and realize I didn’t get to influence my kids the way I wanted to 💔 I refuse for that to be my story!! This break won’t be my last‼️

There’s something about that last kid!! Whether it be number 2, the 3rd, 4th, 5th or even 6th baby. That caboose is something! I’ll never forget the feeling of our family not being complete until we had her 🥰 My Mink Stink ❤️ And yes while we were gone she had another glasses mishap 🤣🤦🏾‍♀️ But she just got her 4th pair yesterday 🤪😒

I’m sure you’ve heard about Florida is being Florida 🤨 

All kinds of measures are being taken to erase some of our history from the curriculum along with banning certain books from our schools. I’ve seen first hand, teachers having to scan their books to make sure their book collections are approved material. Teachers are afraid to speak on certain topics or figures in fear of getting in trouble. But that’s ok….😏 My kids will say what they can’t! 

I filmed each kid how I think they’d be in 11th grade History class but instead of me telling you who is who. I want you to guess who you think Noelle, Lois and Minka are 🤣

“The thing about black history is that the truth is so much more complex than anything you could make up.” – Henry Louis Gates

THREAD LIGHTLY IN MY COMMENTS 👀

#black365 #blackhistorymonth #blackhistory #blackhistorymatters #blackhistoryisamericanhistory

Ok, here’s the 3rd installment of my series “The Subtle Art of Minding Your Own Business”!! The moral of this story is social media is GREAT for inspiration, I mean there’s LOADS of it. But don’t let that inspiration turn into an expectation of you. You may not have this issue as an influencer or even as a regular mom but I was getting caught up in what I “should be doing” and what I “should be buying”! The month away was so refreshing in that I understood so much of the STUFF that I thought was needed or necessary to do this influencer thing was a WHOLE LIE!!! I just needed to get back to what I wanted to say on here. Bringing the conversations in my stories to the main stage. I came back with creativity that I wasn’t expecting. More to come…..

social_posts.post_text: Chalk art but make it Black History facts ‼️ The girls and I have decided to chalk art our way through Black History Month. We started with Mary Elizabeth Bowser, a spy for the Union during the Civil War. Mary was credited by Ulysses S. Grant for her invaluable information during the war. With her photographic memory Mary posed as a slave in the Confederate White House, though she was educated and free. She read top secret documents and over heard conversations that she was privy to because she was never considered a threat. Mary was eventually found out but not before her spying gave the Union the upper hand. On her way out, Mary attempted to burn down the Conference White House. In 1995 Mary was inducted into the Military Intelligence Hall of Fame ✊🏾 #themoreyouknow #blackhistorymonth #blackhistoryfacts #teachourkidsthetruth #black365

What God has for YOU is for YOU!!!!!! 

Listen, every year I said to myself, I pray this is the year my IG blows up 🙄 And guess what, it never happened that way! I was equating that this really big blessing I was looking for would show up in the form of an IG audience that matched my work 😏 Don’t get it twisted, I think my content is great BUT I can’t put God in a square (see what I did there)!! He’s way bigger than that!!!!!! I decided to let go and really let God! Let Him show me what He had for me and not what I wanted for me! So if the kind of success I quantify as “IG success” comes, then cool 🤷🏾‍♀️ but I will never again be unmoved by what God can and WILL do for me in other ways. And of course it goes without saying that I count the health and safety of my family as #1 but you know…..there’s always those things that you just won’t let fully go of and truly give to God, surrendering it to Him to do with it what He wills. Instagram success was that for me. So whether my content ever gets shine or not, I do it because it’s fun and I like it. But NEVER again will I give it the same power I once did!!

She saw the evidence of how resiliency runs through her veins and how fight is apart of our story no matter the subject matter. I have no doubt she’ll make waves and know exactly how she had the courage to 💪🏾 #africanamericanhistorymuseum #blackhistory

Today makes 1 week as Expats! Lessons learned: 
1) Don’t go to the grocery store unprepared, you will waste hours of your life and still get the wrong things 
2) Learn to drive a stick before moving to Portugal 😩 
3) Forget your taste buds in America, just start over (looking at my coffee 👀) 
4) You should probably learn some of the language before moving abroad 🤪 
5) Moving somewhere with nice people is clutch 
6) When they say they are on lunch from 1-3, that’s what they mean, don’t take your happy self up there to those people’s place of business, THEY ARE CLOSED from 1-3
7) No AC is really a thing, learn to sleep hot 😂 (NEVA)!!!!
#expatfamily #blackexpat #blackfamily #livingabroad #lisbonportugal

Oh Madrid, I’ve wanted to visit you forever!! It was short but oh so sweet and you did not disappoint 🇪🇸

This trip involved seeing a bullfight and although I have struggled with the decision as a parent, I’m reminded that traveling the world with our children will have some experiences that are very normal for other children their age. Seeing the world through American eyes is not our goal. Raising our children to be cultured will shock even myself as I see myself as a well traveled adult. Stepping out of the bubble that has its own MANY MANY reasons to be traumatized (i.e active shooter drills at school) will take some getting use to as I discover what is actually a learning experience to be discussed vs something that will traumatize them for life. Honestly, I’m just grateful to have the opportunity 😭 #hazleytravels #madridtravel #expatfamily #expatliving #travelingwithkids

Today marks 1 month in Portugal!!!! I feel like it has both flown by while also feeling like we have LIVED every day of this expat life for the last 31 days. There are so many feelings…

Feeling so far from family but also thanking God for the technology that makes us feel like we’re up the street. 
Feeling the FOMO while also trying to focus on what we have here in front of us. 
Feeling the need to stay up to date on the news while also desperately wanting to separate ourselves from hearing what’s happening in America, like the Jacksonville hate crimes. 
Feeling overjoyed to be out of America while also missing the comforts of home. 
Feeling happy to not feel the pressures of buying all the materialistic things that come with being an American influencer but also wanting all of those said materials 😂
Feeling FINALLY settled and ready to live a normal life here while also wanting nothing to do with normal for the next year. 

Doing hard things is rewarding but it doesn’t come without some rub, without tension. If it was easy, everyone would do it! It’s not a cake walk but the outcome will change how we see the world but it’s definitely going to take some getting use to. #hazleysdoportugal #expatfamily #expatliving #portugalliving #portugalexpats

Oh Versailles 🤩 My family may have been dragged through this experience of seeing you, but I loved every minute 😂 

King Louis XIV has such an interesting story, he built the largest palace in Europe and goes down in history as the longest reigning monarch (72 years), until his death from gangrene. That was fun explaining to the kids 😂 I took care of a patient with gangrene in nursing school and the smell will never leave me (I digress)!! We didn’t listen to the audio guide because I already knew so much about his reign and Marie Antoinette 🤪 Anyone else love this kind of history?!!! 🙋🏾‍♀️ #hazleytravels #blackpassportstamps #blackfamilygoals #blacktravel

When I say this redo of Disneyland Paris was EPIC 🙌🏾😭 We got to experience both of the parks this time, Walt Disney Studios and Disneyland Park! For 2 days we walked until our feet stung and shut down the park! 

It’s been a YEAR 😳 since we’ve been at any Disney Park and man this made me feel at home 🥰 I can’t wait to share all of it but I figured I’d share our favorite rides with you!!! The wait times at Walt Disney Studios were really long compared to the Disneyland Park but when you are use to 200 minute wait times in Orlando, 100 minute wait times don’t scare you too much and seem totally doable 🤪 Plus our girls can handle the wait as long as they are not hungry or sleepy 😅

Honorable mention- Toy Soldiers Parachute Drop (Minka hated it and cried after but Tj says it was good 🤣)

I know my family’s response to this kind of fast paced, work all the time life was extremely drastic and honestly not realistic for a lot of people. This doesn’t mean that to address work life balance you have to quit your job and move out of the country for a year, but it does mean being intentional. 

Lois has been asking for a picnic for probably the better part of a year. But giving it to her seemed overwhelming to even plan. Yes, I know, it’s just a picnic. But I mean when?!! On the 6 days a week her dad was working? Or the overlapping days her mom was working? Or on the one day we all had off together?! But we were EXHAUSTED!! I came up with every excuse not to 😩 

Listen, I definitely don’t have the answers. But in seeing where our family was headed, we decided to yank the steering wheel has hard as we could in the other direction. Do I think we could have been more intentional at home?! Yes, absolutely!!!

When we get back to America, we’ll be facing the same rat race and balancing act but I know this year will shift a lot of our priorities. This post will serve as a reminder to myself that all the girl wanted was a picnic and a picnic we can do 🧺 #hazleysdoportugal #expatliving #expatportugal #familytime

To be fair, I also know my numbers, formal greetings, clothing items, how to ask “where are you from?” “how are you?” AND “my hair is black and curly” 😩🥴

The girls did 5 months of lessons before we moved and they did so well but if Tj and I don’t step it up, we’ll be left in the dust because they are going to be bilingual in no time!! 🎵Now this is story all about how…my Stanley Tumbler cup got lost in the mail🎵 And also the insane process that is shipping things to Portugal!

This was my first attempt to get anything sent here from America and let me tell you……..🙅🏾‍♀️ I don’t need it that bad! 

So the way customs here works is once something has been PAID for to get shipped to you, it then sits in customs FOREVER 😩 before they hit you up and say, “hey, we’ve got a package here for you”. But it doesn’t end there 🤑 You then have to pay MORE money to get it out of customs 😳 But under no circumstances do you refuse the tracking….unless you want to forget you even ordered it in the first place 😒

So….how much did this cup actually cost me after it was all said and done?! Over $84 🤦🏾‍♀️ 

So Stanley cup users….y’all better tell me this cup is going to sing me sweet nothings for what it took to get it here 😩😩😩

Yesterday 😮‍💨😰 If you were watching my stories from yesterday then you saw the saga of how our travel day to London unfolded!!! A heart wrenching tale of how a missed 3 hour flight time and morning arrival turned into 10.5 hours in the airport, hundreds of euros down the drain, an entire day of our vacation wasted and missing nearly HALF of the Elf show we were so excited about!!! 

But probably above all of this we thought we lost Crispy. Crispy put herself in a plastic bag for the girls to find that morning with a note that said “Take me with you”! The girls love being able to take her with us when we travel during the month of December. Lois carried her onto the plane and once we finally arrived in London that evening after having had only airport food and snacks, running on about 3 hours of sleep, we couldn’t find her. I thought for sure Lois had left her on the plane and no one remembers putting her back in the bag. 

The girls asked how she’d find us. I told them she’d probably just go back to the North Pole early and we’d see her next year. I could tell they, specifically Noelle was bummed. I thought about how I could send a letter from the North Pole for the girls to find once we got back to Portugal saying she’d made it back and she loved them and would see them next year. The girls were worried she wouldn’t make it off the plane or out of her plastic bag ☹️ I did everything I could to reassure them that Crispy was capable.

While we were on the train going to the show, I could tell Noelle was holding back tears. I asked her if she was ok and she bursted into tears! She kept saying she wasn’t ready to say goodbye to her yet. Our tradition like many other families is that on Christmas Eve the kids get to touch and hug the Elf which is the only day it’s allowed without ruining her magic. 

I secretly shed a tear next to her as I knew her father and I would be telling her the truth of it all after this Christmas. I was so devastated for it to end this way. Crispy had a couple more tricks up her sleeve before the end of the Christmas season while visiting London! Continued in comments.

I know Switzerland is so last year but I just had to share the last couple of days we had in Switzerland because they were magical 🇨🇭 #hazleytravels #switzerland #switzerlandtravel

So let’s start with the flights, we flew EasyJet on arrival which is a European airline so the cost was a fraction for us coming from Portugal compared to what it would have been coming from America. On the way back, we flew Swiss Airlines, which I will have to say was amazing!!! They gave out Swiss chocolates 🍫 🤤, a toy for the kids and free water! Swiss Airlines does fly to and from America 🇺🇸

Switzerland is EXPENSIVE 😳 Like 7.60 Franks for a Hot Chocolate or 152 Franks to Uber eats Five Guys to our hotel room 🥴 It was a shock to the system!!!! Taxis are extremely expensive and ride share options are limited depending on what part of the country you are traveling in.

Getting around the country is easy using their train system. If you purchase a Swiss Pass it includes all local trains and buses, also the scenic train rides including the Glacier Express that we did!! You do have to reserve the Glacier Express seating which comes with an additional fee of 50 Franks at the time of booking. The Swiss Passes do vary in price as they have classes of seats that you can book. 

They speak 4 major languages that include German, Italian, French and Romansh. There are people there who speak English but don’t be surprised if you encounter many people who do not. They may speak several languages, English not being one of them! Get it together America 🤦🏾‍♀️

This reel is our adventure on the Glacier 3000 and Peak Walk that connects two mountain peaks in the Swiss Alps! With the Swiss Pass you can get the Glacier 3000 ride half off, the Peak Walk is free of charge. It was quite the adventure getting to the suspension bridge with stair cases, lots of snow covered steps and a very very high gondola ride 🚠 

Any questions, let me have them in the comments!!
